The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Spain lead 2-0
Palma de Mallorca: Carlos Moya and Juan Carlos Ferrero gave Spain a 2-0 lead in their Davis Cup quarter-final tie against The Netherlands on Friday. In Lausanne, Switzerland and France were locked 1-1. Swiss world No. 1 Roger Federer beat Nicolas Escude 6-2, 6-4, 6-4 before Arnaud Clement defeated Ivo Heuberger 6-3, 6-3, 6-2. In Minsk, hosts Belarus were leading Argentina 1-0 after Vladimir Voltchkov beat Agustin Calleri 6-3, 6-4, 6-2. Moya gave his home crowd plenty to cheer about as he got his team off to the perfect start with an authoritative performance against Martin Verkerk, winning 6-2, 7-5, 6-4. Juan Carlos Ferrero then beat Raemon Sluiter 6-2, 6-2, 6-4. Moya began confidently, breaking serve in the third and fifth games as he moved Verkerk around the clay court in the converted bullring. Moya looked as though he might wrap things up quickly when he broke twice to take a 4-1 lead in the third. However, Verkerk refused to cave in and levelled at 4-4 The Spaniard proceeded to ease his way into a 5-2 lead before wrapping up the opening set with a flourish when he unleashed his seventh ace. The Mallorcan broke again in the third game of the second set but Verkerk rallied to break back in the sixth after Moya double faulted. Although Verkerk fought hard to earn himself a set point in the tenth game, Moya held his nerve and stepped up a gear before serving out to love to take the second set 7-5.  (Reuters)  Copyright 
